<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
135. 
<taxonomicName LSID="EC516900-B179-51BE-A540-1784807CB350" authority="Regel &amp; Schmahl., Trudy Imp. S. - Peterburgsk. Bot. Sada 6: 339. 1879. (Regel 1879: 339)." authorityName="Regel &amp; Schmahl., Trudy Imp. S. - Peterburgsk. Bot. Sada 6: 339. 1879. (Regel" authorityYear="1879" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus krauseanus" order="Solanales" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="krauseanus">Convolvulus krauseanus Regel &amp; Schmahl., Trudy Imp. S.-Peterburgsk. Bot. Sada 6: 339. 1879. (Regel 1879: 339).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
&quot;near Tashkent&quot;, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Krause</emphasis>
s.n. (syntypes LE!, 2 sheets).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="153" lastPageNumber="154" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="153" lastPageNumber="154" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
Densely grey canescent undershrub with thick woody base, up to 1.5 cm in diameter, from which arise numerous, erect, straight, rigid but not spinescent woody stems to 40 cm, these near leafless upwards and somewhat scape-like. 
<pageBreakToken pageId="153" pageNumber="154" start="start">Leaves</pageBreakToken>
mostly on lower part of stem, numerous, sessile, 5-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, linear to very narrowly linear-oblanceolate, obtuse. Flowers subsessile, 1-5 grouped at the apex of the stem, sometimes with a single flower on the stem below the apical cluster; bracts and peduncles absent; bracteoles 1-2 mm, linear-lanceolate, obtuse; pedicels 1-2 mm; sepals 4-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 mm, broadly ovate to suborbiculate, shortly apiculate, margins scarious, densely silky-pubescent; corolla 1.3-1.5 cm long, white, unlobed but with pilose border, midpetaline bands densely pilose, terminating in teeth; ovary densely pilose; style pilose, divided c. 8 mm above base; stigmas 3 mm. Capsule pilose apically. [
<bibRefCitation author="Petrov, VA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="132 - 150" refId="B265" refString="Petrov, VA, 1935. Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium. Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique 44: 132 - 150" title="Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium." volume="44" year="1935">Petrov 1935</bibRefCitation>
: 139 (plate)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
Endemic to Kyrgyzstan (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Knorring &amp; Minkwitz</emphasis>
s.n. [24/7/1924], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Gudenov</emphasis>
s.n. [19/8/1958], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Botchantsov</emphasis>
78, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Kamelin et al.</emphasis>
9090, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Lazkov</emphasis>
s.n. [4/5/2005]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Very distinct because of the dense grey-canescent indumentum, the plentiful linear leaves and the long, scape-like stem with subsessile flowers at or near the apex</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">The cited type locality is thought to be an error as this species has never subsequently been found near Tashkent (Uzbekistan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
